        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 4:02PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
The Hat, or 40 miles north of Owyhee, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Blackstone Reservoir, Battle Creek Ranch, Gedney Butte, The Hat, Crab
Spring Butte, and Turner Butte.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
